title: Test
summary: This line chart has an x axis representing Year and a y axis representing Unemployment rate, with a total of 21 data points.
Overall Unemployment rate has decreased over the Year.

Unemployment rate is roughly constant from 1999 to 2001, roughly decreasing from 2001 to 2002, roughly constant from 2002 to 2004, rapidly decreasing from 2004 to 2007, slightly increasing from 2007 to 2009, roughly constant from 2009 to 2015, slightly decreasing from 2015 to 2017, and lastly roughly constant from 2017 to 2019.
The steepest increase occurs in between the Year 2008 and 2009.
Max Unemployment rate about 15.34 was recorded at Year 2002
Min Unemployment rate about 13.69 was recorded at Year 2008
This line chart has an x axis representing Year and a y axis representing Unemployment rate, with a total of 21 data points. The chart has 4 significant trends.
The longest trend is moderately decreasing which exists from 2013 to 2019.
On the other hand, the next significant trend is slightly decreasing which exists from 2002 to 2008.
On the other hand, the next significant trend is extremely increasing which exists from 2008 to 2013.
